 For the "4.9/5 Stars" badge:
      The background is set on line 22:
   1     <div className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary/10 text-primary px-4 py-2 rounded-full mb-8">
      The class bg-primary/10 applies the primary color (which is a teal color) with 10% opacity.

   2. For the "Watch: 3-Year-Old Reads First Word" section:
      The background is a gradient set on line 51:

   1     <div className="aspect-video bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/20 to-accent/20 rounded-xl flex items-center 
     justify-center mb-4">
      The classes from-primary/20 and to-accent/20 create a gradient using the primary (teal) and accent colors, both with
  20% opacity.

   3. For the "Total Value: $500+" section:
      The background is set on line 198:

   1     <div className="text-center mt-12 bg-primary/5 rounded-2xl p-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto border-2 border-primary/20"
     >
      The class bg-primary/5 applies the primary (teal) color with 5% opacity.

  In Tailwind CSS, the / notation after a color (like bg-primary/10) is used to set the opacity of the color.